<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">311. Brooklyn Botanic Garden. Natural Plant Dyeing: A Handbook. Brooklyn,1973. 64 pp. Index, bibl., B/W illus. color illus. </p><p class="annot">This handbook was originally a collection of articles published inPlants &Gardens, volume 29, number 2. Experts discuss a wide range of issues mainly related to collecting and using natural materials in the United States, Sweden, Australia, and New Zealand. Also useful is illustrated information on mordants and how their use can yield diverse results from the same dyebath. This handbook will be most valuable to those interested in locating and using natural plant materials for dyeing. The annotated bibliography suggests seven additional resources on the topic and a list of dye plant suppliers is also included. </p></div>
